FuncDef: This command configures the QinQ Ethertype on the PW-port. The PW-port is used to extract a customer's Ethernet traffic that is transported in a tunnel over an IP/MPLS network. Theqinq-etyperepresents the first two bytes (TPID) in the outer 801.1Q header of the double-tagged Ethernet frame inside the tunnel.

ParaDef.Info: The value for the qinq-etype field, in hexadecimal format. Values-0x0600..0xFFFF. ParamDefault: Default- 0x8100
